SIMPLE: tumbril
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tumbril
<hw>Tum"bril</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>tomberel</ets>, F.
<ets>tombereau</ets>, fr. <ets>tomber</ets> to fall, to tumble; of
Teutonic origin. Cf. <er>Tumble</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cucking
stool for the punishment of scolds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rough cart.</def> <rj><au>Tusser.</au>
<au>Tatler.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A cart or carriage with two
wheels, which accompanies troops or artillery, to convey the tools of
pioneers, cartridges, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A kind of basket or cage of osiers, willows, or the
like, to hold hay and other food for sheep.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tumefacient</ent>⟦br⟧
